text:
24th Drive (foreground, not shown), between 19th and 21st Streets, showing in the foreground Emily P. Woolsey's gardener's cottage. In the background is Mallison's Silk Mill facing Twenty-fourth Ave.
1922.
Eumene L. Armbruster Collection.

24th Drive, west from 21st Street to 19th Street and Astoria Park, showing new homes in Astoria. In the background
is the Hellgate Bridge.
Ewing Galloway  About 1927

24th Terrace, south side, east from 19th to 21st Streets, showing the demolition of brick homes for the construction of the Triborough Bridge. 24th Terrace, a one-block thoroughfare formerly called Park Terrace, was obliterated when the bridge was constructed.
P. L. Sperr  May 27, 1934
title: Queens: 24th Terrace - 19th Street
